This is going to be 1/36 minus 1/49.

00:05:13.766 --> 00:05:14.900
Then we're going to have

00:05:14.900 --> 00:05:19.900
minus 1/64 minus ...

00:05:20.033 --> 00:05:21.033
Actually, the next terms is going to be

00:05:21.033 --> 00:05:23.933
one over nine squared, 1/81.

00:05:24.566 --> 00:05:27.079
Then minus, and we keep going like that,

00:05:27.100 --> 00:05:30.200
on and on and on, on
and on and on, forever.

00:05:30.566 --> 00:05:31.866
Now, notice what happens.

00:05:32.300 --> 00:05:35.000
This, this term right over here

00:05:35.301 --> 00:05:36.600
is positive.

00:05:37.433 --> 00:05:39.900
We have a smaller number

00:05:39.900 --> 00:05:41.533
being subtracted from a larger number.

00:05:42.300 --> 00:05:44.466
This term right over here is positive.

00:05:45.100 --> 00:05:46.666
We're staring with 1/25,

00:05:46.966 --> 00:05:48.100
and then we're subtracting

00:05:48.100 --> 00:05:50.600
a bunch of positive things from it.

00:05:51.167 --> 00:05:55.400
This thing has to be less than 1/25.

